WEBVTT

00:01.826 --> 00:04.849
Two weeks ago, it was Taylor Swift.

00:06.651 --> 00:08.472
Last week, it was the Big Bang Theory.

00:10.254 --> 00:13.457
This week, we are beginning with the Wizard of Oz.

00:15.379 --> 00:17.521
Now, I hope that most of you are familiar with the movie.

00:18.082 --> 00:18.843
It's a classic.

00:18.883 --> 00:28.952
It was released in 1939, yet year after year, because it is such a good movie, it continues to play over and over again on TV.

00:28.973 --> 00:30.514
It's an engaging story.

00:31.202 --> 00:43.614
a tornado rips through Kansas, and the main character Dorsey and her dog Toto in their house are transported via tornado to the magical land of Oz.

00:44.875 --> 00:56.847
When they get to Oz, they realize that they need to return to Kansas so they begin traveling on the yellow brick road to the Emerald City to meet with the wizard who is going to help them get back to Kansas.

00:57.888 --> 01:00.370
In route, they meet a scarecrow who needs a brain

01:01.186 --> 01:07.634
They meet a tin man who needs a heart, and they meet a cowardly lion who wants courage.

01:08.656 --> 01:14.123
And together they journey along the yellow brick road to the Emerald City to fulfill their longing.

01:15.364 --> 01:21.272
And it's an interesting story, not just the story itself, but all these characters in the story are interesting.

01:21.572 --> 01:29.042
They draw us into the story as viewers, because there's so much about the characters that we can relate with.

01:31.458 --> 01:36.563
Who doesn't at one time in their life or another long for home?

01:38.945 --> 01:40.987
Many people want to be more intelligent.

01:42.369 --> 01:49.796
Some people want to be more compassionate, but I think it's the lion.

01:51.798 --> 01:56.002
I think it's the lion that resonates most with many of us.

01:58.004 --> 01:59.986
Who doesn't want more courage?

02:01.794 --> 02:03.556
All of us want more courage.

02:03.576 --> 02:17.153
So this lion in the story resonates, resonates with you and me because we live lives wanting to be more courageous.

02:18.335 --> 02:19.216
Take a look at this clip.

02:21.899 --> 02:23.001
Here, here.

02:23.201 --> 02:24.242
Go ahead and let us alone.

02:24.262 --> 02:25.223
Oh, scared, huh?

02:25.824 --> 02:26.465
Afraid, huh?

02:27.726 --> 02:30.610
How long can you stay fresh in that can?

02:31.202 --> 02:34.707
Come on, get up and fight your shivering junkyard.

02:36.209 --> 02:38.873
Put your hands up your lopsided bag of hay.

02:38.893 --> 02:40.435
No, that's getting personal, iron.

02:41.637 --> 02:43.519
Yes, get up and teach him a lesson.

02:43.900 --> 02:46.684
Well, what's wrong with you teaching them?

02:46.744 --> 02:50.449
Well, I hardly know them.

02:50.469 --> 02:56.818
Well, I'll get you anyway, Peewee.

03:02.530 --> 03:06.275
What did you do that for?

03:06.295 --> 03:08.498
I didn't buy them.

03:08.518 --> 03:09.959
No, but you tried to.

03:10.400 --> 03:14.465
It's bad enough picking on a straw man, but when you go around picking on poor little dog.

03:14.505 --> 03:18.731
Well, you didn't have to go and hit me, did you?

03:18.751 --> 03:20.713
Is my nose bleeding?

03:20.733 --> 03:21.875
Well, of course not.

03:24.538 --> 03:27.262
My goodness, what a first you're making.

03:27.322 --> 03:30.706
Well, actually, when you go around picking on things weaker than you are,

03:31.490 --> 03:33.413
Why, you're nothing but a great big collar.

03:33.553 --> 03:34.194
You're right.

03:34.415 --> 03:35.456
I have a collar.

03:37.159 --> 03:38.661
I haven't any courage at all.

03:38.681 --> 03:41.185
I even scare myself.

03:43.209 --> 03:45.092
Look at the cycles under my eyes.

03:45.112 --> 03:46.975
I haven't slept in weeks.

03:47.535 --> 03:49.619
Why don't you try counting sheep?

03:49.639 --> 03:50.921
That doesn't do any good.

03:50.961 --> 03:54.306
I'm afraid of them.

03:54.326 --> 03:55.448
Oh, that's too bad.

03:56.910 --> 03:59.314
Don't you think the wizard could help him, too?

03:59.426 --> 04:00.568
I don't see why not.

04:01.729 --> 04:03.051
Why don't you come along with us?

04:03.291 --> 04:06.376
We're on our way to see the wizard now, to get him a heart.

04:06.396 --> 04:07.237
And him a brain.

04:07.477 --> 04:09.200
I'm sure he could give you some courage.

04:10.722 --> 04:11.923
It's funny.

04:13.225 --> 04:13.926
But I hope you caught it.

04:13.946 --> 04:15.809
There's a powerful exchange in there.

04:16.490 --> 04:21.056
The Tin Man says to the lion, why don't you try counting sheep?

04:21.977 --> 04:23.980
And the lion responds, that doesn't do any good.

04:24.140 --> 04:28.146
I'm afraid of that.

04:28.578 --> 04:31.162
When I saw that, yeah, it's funny.

04:33.306 --> 04:37.052
But it reminded me that all of us are afraid of something.

04:38.233 --> 04:42.901
Now, maybe you're not afraid of sheep, but you're likely afraid of something.

04:44.624 --> 04:56.082
Maybe you're afraid of heights like I am, or maybe you're afraid of the dark or thunder, or maybe you're afraid of

04:56.514 --> 04:59.137
enclosed spaces or flying.

05:00.559 --> 05:03.983
Maybe you're afraid of spiders or snakes.

05:06.005 --> 05:12.633
Maybe you're afraid of other people's opinions or rejection or being alone.

05:14.436 --> 05:17.640
Maybe you're afraid of going to the doctor, afraid of what she's going to tell you.

05:19.482 --> 05:23.026
Maybe, maybe you're afraid to die.

05:25.698 --> 05:28.202
You see, all of us are afraid of something.

05:29.363 --> 05:31.787
And fear can be incapacitating.

05:32.748 --> 05:39.998
Fear can paralyze us from doing the things that we should be doing, especially the things that God has called us to do.

05:41.921 --> 05:48.630
Fear can cause us to be hesitant, can cause us to be reserved, to cause us to stay in place.

05:49.451 --> 05:54.258
So like that cowardly lion, we want to have courage.

05:54.722 --> 05:58.126
We want to live a life standing up against our fears.

05:58.606 --> 06:02.411
We want to live a life engaged in what is going on around us.

06:02.751 --> 06:06.815
We want to live a life doing the things that God has called us to do.

06:07.156 --> 06:09.238
We want to live courageously.

06:10.440 --> 06:11.981
Do you want to live courageously?

06:13.843 --> 06:16.006
Do you want to live a life that is full of courage?

06:17.207 --> 06:18.949
Do you want to overcome your fears?

06:20.451 --> 06:21.392
Of course you do.

06:21.432 --> 06:23.474
We all do.

06:23.970 --> 06:28.557
We all want to live a life that is more courageous.

06:31.322 --> 06:40.036
The good news is that this morning God, through the Apostle John, tells us exactly how to do that.

06:41.138 --> 06:49.131
So let's see what John has to say to us this morning to help us live a life that is full of courage.

06:49.411 --> 06:51.154
So if you would, would you take your Bible

06:51.650 --> 06:56.735
and would you turn to 1 John 4, 1 John 4?

06:57.796 --> 07:08.107
If you do not have a Bible, there's one in the rock in front of you, grab that Bible, open it up to page 988, and there you will find the verses that we're going to be looking at this morning.

07:08.788 --> 07:17.456
Now, I need to warn you right at the front before we get started that John's prescription is probably not what you would expect.

07:18.117 --> 07:19.058
It's interesting.

07:19.682 --> 07:26.632
Scripture doesn't tell us to conquer fear through strength or even through spiritual performance.

07:27.433 --> 07:33.462
It doesn't tell us to repress it, to ignore it, or even fake our way through it.

07:33.742 --> 07:40.172
John isn't going to tell us to read a book or to go to counseling or to face our fears.

07:41.353 --> 07:44.698
John has something much more radical to tell us this morning.

07:45.640 --> 07:47.282
This morning, John

07:47.394 --> 07:55.303
tells us that perfect love casts out or perfect love drives out fear.

07:57.465 --> 08:02.330
That means that the key to courage isn't more power.

08:03.251 --> 08:04.773
It's not more control.

08:05.554 --> 08:07.596
It's not even more clarity.

08:08.477 --> 08:13.042
The key to courage is love.

08:14.690 --> 08:22.562
over these past few weeks, we've been looking at the truth, at the fact, at the reality that God is love.

08:23.103 --> 08:29.553
Not just that God is loving, but that God Himself is love.

08:30.054 --> 08:39.007
And this morning, we're gonna dig a little deeper into what that means for you and for me in regard to driving out fear.

08:39.067 --> 08:43.474
And what we learn about God's love is that perfect love

08:44.130 --> 08:46.233
drives out fear.

08:48.256 --> 08:51.300
We're in the same verses that we've been in the past few weeks.

08:52.001 --> 08:55.586
This morning, we're going to focus on verses 15 through 19.

08:56.507 --> 09:01.894
So follow along, as I read, 1 John 4, beginning in verse 15.

09:03.357 --> 09:08.524
If anyone acknowledges that Jesus is the Son of God, God lives in them and they in God.

09:09.144 --> 09:13.170
And so we know and rely on the love of God and the love God has for us.

09:13.602 --> 09:15.044
God is love.

09:15.604 --> 09:18.228
Whoever lives in love lives in God and God in them.

09:18.248 --> 09:24.055
This is how love is made complete among us so that we will have confidence on the day of judgment.

09:24.755 --> 09:26.718
In this world, we are like Jesus.

09:27.178 --> 09:33.226
There is no fear in love, but perfect love drives out fear because fear has to do with punishment.

09:33.946 --> 09:36.510
The one who fears is not made perfect in love.

09:37.050 --> 09:40.274
We love because he first loved us.

09:40.834 --> 09:52.847
Now we're gonna dig deeper into these verses and as we dig deeper into these verses, I want you to see that it is the love of God and our love for others that drives out fear.

09:53.849 --> 10:04.340
If you want to live courageously, you must live in, you must rely upon God's love for you and you must live a life loving others.

10:05.622 --> 10:09.426
Living in the love of God and loving others

10:09.826 --> 10:11.608
drives out fear.

10:13.591 --> 10:18.999
So first, let's look at how God's love drives out fear.

10:19.379 --> 10:20.360
Look again at verse 15.

10:21.822 --> 10:27.690
If anyone acknowledges that Jesus is the Son of God, God lives in them and they in God.

10:28.532 --> 10:29.933
Now you see that word acknowledges?

10:31.375 --> 10:32.036
Underline that.

10:32.056 --> 10:35.821
It's a key word in our passage and in verse 15.

10:35.841 --> 10:39.186
This is necessary

10:39.362 --> 10:43.846
to living fully in the love of God.

10:43.866 --> 10:50.273
If you do not acknowledge Jesus, you will not live fully in the love of God.

10:51.034 --> 10:58.941
In the original language, this word acknowledges, or some of your translations may say confesses, was a legal term.

10:59.662 --> 11:05.608
It meant to say the same, to agree with or to consent.

11:06.229 --> 11:07.730
It was a legal term

11:07.906 --> 11:16.881
that was used to affirm or to agree with the statement of another, like confessing guilt before a judge or a jury.

11:17.862 --> 11:25.475
It came to be used in a similar way in Scripture to acknowledge or to confess sin is to say the same.

11:25.936 --> 11:30.924
It's to agree with God about our sin and about our guilt.

11:31.645 --> 11:34.770
It's also used to acknowledge

11:34.882 --> 11:38.187
or confess that Jesus is the Son of God.

11:38.287 --> 11:46.618
It's saying the same thing as God says about His Son, that He is truly the Son of God.

11:46.638 --> 11:57.473
This acknowledgement or this confession is saying the same thing about our sin and about Jesus.

11:58.915 --> 12:00.818
So when we acknowledge

12:01.026 --> 12:04.310
or confess Jesus as Savior and Lord.

12:04.330 --> 12:04.911
Do you see it?

12:04.931 --> 12:05.592
Look what it says.

12:06.092 --> 12:09.016
God lives in them and they and God.

12:09.076 --> 12:11.759
And then look at verse 16.

12:11.779 --> 12:15.123
And so we know and rely on the love God has for us.

12:16.385 --> 12:18.227
And God is love.

12:19.108 --> 12:24.014
And God comes to live inside of us and his love comes to live in us.

12:25.035 --> 12:30.482
And so his love resides in us to know God

12:30.914 --> 12:32.737
is to know love.

12:34.740 --> 12:42.392
So for all of us who acknowledge Jesus, God's love abides in us.

12:43.313 --> 12:46.498
So we no longer have to be afraid.

12:47.280 --> 12:50.565
And there should be no fear of punishment.

12:51.246 --> 12:52.528
That's verse 17.

12:53.329 --> 12:55.072
Yes, we sin.

12:55.132 --> 12:56.594
And yes,

12:56.706 --> 12:58.468
there is guilt from that sin.

12:58.809 --> 13:07.960
But because we have acknowledged or confessed Jesus and turned from our sin, put our faith in Him, we're forgiven.

13:08.861 --> 13:14.588
So now when God our heavenly Father looks at us, He no longer sees our sin.

13:14.648 --> 13:19.834
He now looks at us and He sees the righteousness of Jesus Christ.

13:21.276 --> 13:26.322
He sees Jesus and not us.

13:26.786 --> 13:34.837
means that we are covered by the love of God, which brings us to verse 18.

13:35.739 --> 13:36.460
Look what it says.

13:37.361 --> 13:45.032
There is no fear in love, but perfect love drives out fear because fear has to do with punishment.

13:45.593 --> 13:48.577
The one who fears is not made perfect in love.

13:49.458 --> 13:53.323
God is love, and that perfect love drives out fear.

13:53.984 --> 13:55.186
We sometimes assume

13:56.162 --> 14:00.929
that this passage is primarily about our ability to love better.

14:01.610 --> 14:05.636
But it's ultimately about the love that God has for us.

14:06.297 --> 14:08.500
We've seen this all throughout this chapter.

14:09.221 --> 14:11.364
Earlier in chapter four, look back at verse 10.

14:12.326 --> 14:18.735
Verse 10 says, this is love, not that we loved God, but that He loved us.

14:19.697 --> 14:23.562
Perfect love does not originate in you or me.

14:24.103 --> 14:26.066
Perfect love originates

14:26.242 --> 14:34.212
In God, the word perfect here, it means full, mature, whole, complete.

14:34.893 --> 14:35.994
It's a perfect love.

14:36.635 --> 14:39.679
It's about what it gives, not what it gets.

14:40.380 --> 14:50.233
It's the kind of love that doesn't flinch when it sees your mess, the kind of love that already knows your weaknesses and has already made provision for them.

14:51.414 --> 14:54.578
God's perfect love is not shallow.

14:54.978 --> 14:56.580
It's not performative.

14:57.321 --> 14:59.483
It's not withdrawn when you fail.

14:59.823 --> 15:02.666
It does not punish you for being human.

15:03.047 --> 15:06.250
It does not abandon you when you struggle.

15:07.431 --> 15:14.239
You see, God's perfect love is rooted in the finished work of Jesus Christ.

15:14.859 --> 15:18.463
And it comes to complete what fear has broken.

15:18.523 --> 15:24.690
And when you and I, when we start living in that love, when we rely on that love,

15:24.930 --> 15:27.854
fear will no longer run the show.

15:29.256 --> 15:34.444
Because we are experiencing the fullness of God's love in our lives.

15:34.845 --> 15:36.187
God loves us.

15:36.607 --> 15:41.194
So there is no reason to be afraid of anything.

15:41.815 --> 15:44.299
So when fear comes whispering, I know you've had this.

15:45.440 --> 15:51.089
I know in your life fear has come whispering and you have heard fear say to you, you're not safe.

15:53.232 --> 15:54.834
Or you're going to be rejected.

15:55.714 --> 15:57.436
or you're going to be judged.

15:58.999 --> 16:00.180
Love answers back.

16:00.521 --> 16:01.742
God answers back.

16:02.183 --> 16:04.005
No, that's not the case.

16:04.386 --> 16:05.608
You are mine.

16:07.851 --> 16:13.538
And there is no reason to fear because of the love that I have for you.

16:15.501 --> 16:16.783
I'd like you to think about it this way.

16:18.665 --> 16:21.970
When you're at work and your boss

16:22.306 --> 16:25.811
thinks you're doing a good job and your boss likes you.

16:25.851 --> 16:29.896
It really doesn't matter what your coworkers think doesn't.

16:31.478 --> 16:34.943
Because your boss thinks you're great at home.

16:35.443 --> 16:37.145
If your wife thinks you're the best.

16:43.073 --> 16:43.834
I got a thumbs up.

16:44.255 --> 16:49.842
If your wife thinks you're the best, again, it really doesn't matter what other people think.

16:51.138 --> 17:03.477
And when the creator of the universe loves you with a perfect love, there is absolutely nothing, absolutely nothing that you should be afraid of.

17:03.497 --> 17:06.762
Now I know this is hard.

17:07.603 --> 17:11.930
I know this is hard for some of you because maybe you grew up with an overly strict father.

17:13.031 --> 17:17.598
Or you learned a lot of incorrect legalistic teachings about God.

17:18.400 --> 17:19.922
But let me tell you,

17:20.834 --> 17:27.121
The God of the Bible is a God who is full of a perfect love for you.

17:27.141 --> 17:31.847
He loves you from the top of your head to the bottom of your toes.

17:32.147 --> 17:34.230
He loves you inside and out.

17:35.451 --> 17:41.598
And because of his perfect love for you, there is nothing for you or I to be afraid of.

17:43.140 --> 17:44.722
Now, yes, he is holy.

17:45.602 --> 17:54.251
And yes, he disciplines his children, but he doesn't discipline his children out of a position of judgment or hate or angst.

17:54.271 --> 18:01.158
He comes from a position of love where he is looking to right our wrong and put us back on the right path.

18:02.079 --> 18:09.827
It's why Paul is able to write in Romans 8 chapter 1, which may be the best verse in all of the Bible.

18:10.108 --> 18:10.968
Paul writes this.

18:11.048 --> 18:12.530
He writes, therefore,

18:12.770 --> 18:15.813
There is now, not some, not a little.

18:16.133 --> 18:22.299
Therefore, there is now no condemnation for those who are in Christ Jesus.

18:23.280 --> 18:30.147
If you have acknowledged Jesus Christ as your Lord and Savior, there is no condemnation.

18:32.629 --> 18:42.258
And you and I are able to live fully and completely in the perfect love of God which drives out fear.

18:43.394 --> 18:46.919
There's a story in John's gospel that he recounts.

18:46.959 --> 18:50.284
It's one of my favorite stories in all of the Bible.

18:51.867 --> 18:54.110
There is a woman who is caught in adultery.

18:55.312 --> 18:57.475
And her guilt doesn't seem to be questioned.

18:58.257 --> 19:00.560
She is caught in adultery.

19:01.502 --> 19:03.845
And there's a group of men that bring her to Jesus.

19:03.865 --> 19:07.010
Now at the time, Jesus is talking and he's teaching a large crowd.

19:07.050 --> 19:12.338
And this group of men, they bring this woman to Jesus and they kind of throw her at his feet and they're like,

19:12.546 --> 19:14.408
Hey, what are you gonna do about this?

19:16.912 --> 19:18.353
This woman committed adultery.

19:22.619 --> 19:24.942
Now, can we think about what the woman was feeling at that time?

19:29.468 --> 19:30.869
Can you think about the humiliation?

19:34.594 --> 19:37.978
How about the fear?

19:37.998 --> 19:40.882
The Mosaic law said that she should be stoned for that sin.

19:45.890 --> 19:51.738
But Jesus, Jesus looks at the crowd.

19:53.179 --> 19:57.685
He looks at the men and he bends down.

20:00.729 --> 20:02.211
And he starts writing in the sand.

20:07.138 --> 20:13.586
And then he looks up at everyone and he says, you without sin.

20:15.202 --> 20:16.284
can throw the first down.

20:19.969 --> 20:21.011
And then he looks back down.

20:23.294 --> 20:23.935
And he's writing.

20:26.660 --> 20:35.233
A couple of minutes later, still kneeling, he says to the woman, where are they?

20:38.578 --> 20:39.600
You see, they had all left.

20:42.244 --> 20:43.826
He asked, did any of them condemn you?

20:46.658 --> 20:47.579
She said, no one, sir.

20:50.443 --> 20:51.625
And he said, neither do I.

20:53.187 --> 20:54.689
Go and send Omar.

21:00.277 --> 21:03.141
That is the perfect love of God.

21:06.185 --> 21:15.218
And notice, God in human flesh stayed kneeling

21:16.578 --> 21:20.945
while he spoke to the woman.

21:20.965 --> 21:23.088
He didn't rise up and stand up over her.

21:25.693 --> 21:30.220
He stayed kneeling and he's like, I don't condemn you either.

21:31.662 --> 21:33.144
Go and sin no more.

21:35.408 --> 21:38.493
That is the perfect love of God.

21:40.536 --> 21:41.638
That's how he loves you.

21:43.621 --> 21:44.242
Therefore,

21:44.802 --> 21:51.030
there is now no condemnation for those who are in Christ Jesus.

21:53.534 --> 22:05.970
And because He loves you with that deep and great love, there is no reason to be afraid of anything.

22:10.356 --> 22:12.018
Now, it seems like we could stop here.

22:14.242 --> 22:19.171
but there is a second part of driving out fear in our lives.

22:20.173 --> 22:21.355
And we don't want to miss it.

22:21.956 --> 22:25.583
So take your Bible and turn or look at verse 17.

22:26.725 --> 22:33.217
Verse 17 says, this is how love is made complete among us so that we will have confidence on the day of judgment.

22:34.059 --> 22:38.066
In this world, we are like Jesus.

22:38.338 --> 22:40.541
underline that phrase.

22:40.682 --> 22:44.087
In this world, we are like Jesus.

22:44.408 --> 22:46.431
What does it mean to be like Jesus?

22:47.432 --> 23:02.616
It means that in this sinful world that we live in, we will talk like Jesus talked, we will walk like Jesus walked, we will live like Jesus lived, and we will love as Jesus loves.

23:03.257 --> 23:06.162
That's why John writes verse 19.

23:06.306 --> 23:16.438
We love because He first loved us, because Jesus loves us, because we experience this perfect love from God the Father.

23:16.478 --> 23:22.946
The call on our lives is to go out and love others just like Jesus loved them.

23:22.986 --> 23:31.156
And the only way that you can love an unlovely person is if the love of God, if God Himself is in you.

23:31.997 --> 23:32.658
Remember.

23:33.058 --> 23:39.325
God is love and God loves you, but this love is not for your exclusive benefit.

23:39.685 --> 23:41.367
It's not just for you.

23:41.407 --> 23:48.595
This love that God has for you is meant for you to share with the people that God brings into your life.

23:48.675 --> 23:56.744
It is meant to share with people that you come in contact with day after day, whether they are lovely or whether they are unlovely.

23:57.185 --> 24:02.130
God loves you so that like Jesus, you can love others.

24:02.658 --> 24:10.633
And when you love others in the way that God loves you, you will not fear.

24:10.653 --> 24:12.757
It is how love works.

24:13.399 --> 24:19.410
The first aspect of driving out fear is relying upon and living in the fullness

24:19.490 --> 24:33.960
of God's love, the second aspect or instruction is recognizing that when I use God's perfect love and love other people that are in my life, that too is going to drive out fear.

24:34.321 --> 24:36.185
Let's think about how this works.

24:37.367 --> 24:39.231
How many of you are parents?

24:39.291 --> 24:40.754
If you're a parent, raise your hand.

24:41.282 --> 24:41.622
Great.

24:41.883 --> 24:45.987
If you're not a parent, the illustration will make sense to you, so please hang on.

24:46.407 --> 24:53.995
If you're a parent, that means right now you have a young child, or at one point in time, you had a young child.

24:54.736 --> 24:59.160
Now, when your child was young, did your child ever get sick?

25:03.705 --> 25:04.806
Let's engage with each other.

25:04.846 --> 25:05.366
It helps me.

25:06.287 --> 25:07.208
Thank you.

25:07.228 --> 25:08.850
Did your child ever get sick?

25:09.698 --> 25:19.367
And when your child got sick, maybe it was a cold, maybe the flu, maybe COVID, maybe it was some more serious infectious disease.

25:20.168 --> 25:23.071
When your child got sick, did you care for her?

25:24.132 --> 25:25.753
Yes, you cared for her.

25:26.154 --> 25:32.199
And while you were caring for her, did it ever cross your mind that you were going to get sick?

25:32.239 --> 25:35.743
Did you even care whether you got sick with what they had?

25:35.763 --> 25:38.165
No, probably not.

25:38.585 --> 25:39.186
Why?

25:40.482 --> 25:45.729
Because your perfect love for your child drove out that fear.

25:45.769 --> 25:50.194
It was a number of years ago, we were celebrating Christmas.

25:50.234 --> 25:52.157
We were at Jen's family's house.

25:53.058 --> 26:01.929
And my oldest son, Jeff, I think he was about eight at the time, is the end of the day and he comes up to me and he's like, Dad, I'm not really feeling well.

26:02.730 --> 26:08.818
Well, he was right because no sooner did he get those words out than he threw up all over the place.

26:09.762 --> 26:12.285
And over me.

26:12.305 --> 26:24.098
So I like, like we jump into action, we kind of clean up all the throw up, but it's just not, it's just not that one, like if you're a parent, you know this, like eight year olds don't just throw up once.

26:25.399 --> 26:27.141
Like he threw up all night.

26:28.602 --> 26:34.509
So Jen and I, Jeff and I spent the night in the family room.

26:34.529 --> 26:35.350
He was throwing up.

26:36.551 --> 26:39.314
I was cleaning up and just holding on and loving it.

26:41.058 --> 26:47.026
And there wasn't one time during that night that I was concerned that I was going to get whatever he had.

26:48.608 --> 26:48.849
Why?

26:50.311 --> 26:51.132
Because I love him.

26:52.273 --> 26:56.479
And the love that I have for my son drove out that fear.

26:57.520 --> 27:00.444
If you are a parent, you know exactly what I'm talking about.

27:01.566 --> 27:03.388
But here is the thing in the instruction.

27:03.428 --> 27:04.590
Now I know what you're saying.

27:04.610 --> 27:05.632
You're saying you're in your mind with time.

27:06.613 --> 27:07.214
That's easy.

27:07.814 --> 27:08.515
He's your son.

27:08.555 --> 27:10.418
Of course you love him.

27:11.490 --> 27:22.226
But if we are to be like Jesus, and we are to love others like Jesus loves other people, our love is not just limited to our immediate family members.

27:22.690 --> 27:26.514
We are called to love everyone that God brings into our path.

27:26.574 --> 27:30.359
And even people that He doesn't bring into our path, that we go out and find.

27:30.379 --> 27:33.062
We are called not to love just the lovely.

27:33.322 --> 27:35.384
We are called to love the unlovely.

27:35.705 --> 27:42.232
And when you do the beautiful thing is that that love will drive out any fear that you have.

27:45.656 --> 27:47.418
But sometimes we think that it's not possible.

27:48.680 --> 27:50.802
But I will tell you, it was possible in the early church

27:51.426 --> 27:58.336
in the early 4th century, in the city of Caesarea, following a war and famine, the city was struck by the plague.

27:59.297 --> 28:06.888
The plague comes and people all throughout the city start dying, so the wealthy people, they leave the city for the safety of the countryside.

28:07.328 --> 28:11.915
Well, during the Exodus, there is one group of people who remains in Caesarea.

28:11.995 --> 28:14.739
Any idea who the people who remained in Caesarea were?

28:16.161 --> 28:17.042
The Christians.

28:17.186 --> 28:23.995
The Christians stayed in Caesarea to care for those who were dying and sick.

28:24.997 --> 28:30.083
Eusebius, the bishop of Caesarea, and an ancient historian records it this way.

28:30.364 --> 28:31.265
Look what he writes.

28:33.027 --> 28:38.655
All day long, some of them, the Christians, tended to the dying and to their burial.

28:39.116 --> 28:41.759
Countless numbers with no one to care for them.

28:42.720 --> 28:46.866
Others gathered together from all parts of the city, a multitude

28:46.946 --> 28:53.635
of those withered from famine and distributed bread to them all."

28:53.655 --> 29:08.476
Eusebius goes on to state that because of their love and compassion in the midst of the plague, quote, the Christian's deeds were on everyone's lips and they glorified the God of the Christians.

29:09.477 --> 29:09.938
These

29:10.050 --> 29:15.236
Early Christians' love for others drove out their fear of the plague.

29:15.636 --> 29:23.445
It drove out their fear of dying and their love led other people to glorify God.

29:26.428 --> 29:32.555
I am wondering if historians will write the same thing about us.

29:38.221 --> 29:39.442
I'm not so sure they will.

29:40.482 --> 29:47.149
Now I know, I know there are some of you who love others with the perfect love of God.

29:47.869 --> 29:58.600
You are out, you are engaging, you are engaging others with a sacrificial love that points people to Jesus, that causes them to glorify God.

29:58.940 --> 30:03.365
And as a result of your love for others, you do not live in fear.

30:03.625 --> 30:06.608
You live a life that is full of courage.

30:07.949 --> 30:08.850
But for some,

30:09.474 --> 30:23.300
And for much of the evangelical church, I think many are focused almost exclusively on self-interest and are not demonstrating sacrificial love to people around them.

30:25.404 --> 30:26.506
It happens in the church.

30:27.989 --> 30:30.674
Think about the divide that we have in sometimes over worship.

30:31.970 --> 30:39.618
Instead, love would say, I'm more concerned with the preference of the person next to me than I am with my own preference.

30:41.480 --> 30:45.023
Think about minor, minor theological disputes.

30:46.565 --> 30:53.812
Love would call us to sit down and discuss and talk through and resolve those disputes.

30:55.114 --> 30:59.538
Think about those who are trying to create a circle of homogeneity

31:00.226 --> 31:03.752
where love would include others in our midst.

31:06.877 --> 31:11.584
Remember, it is perfect love that casts out fear.

31:11.985 --> 31:21.259
And when you live with the self-focus and self-interest and a selfishness, the fear is just going to continue to grow inside of you.

31:22.441 --> 31:28.050
And I think I may be even more concerned with what is happening when we engage with those outside the church.

31:30.882 --> 31:31.643
Question for you.

31:33.605 --> 31:40.071
Do people know you more for your political opinions or for the fact that you're a follower of Jesus?

31:45.596 --> 31:53.203
Do you talk more about your favorite political leader or about Jesus?

31:58.007 --> 32:00.690
Does your hat have a political slogan on it?

32:01.410 --> 32:06.457
Or does it have a patch that says, Jesus loves you and so do I.

32:11.204 --> 32:19.235
All of that stuff is just going to make you more afraid.

32:19.275 --> 32:23.681
You follow that you will live in fear.

32:24.723 --> 32:27.026
The encouragement for us this morning

32:27.106 --> 32:41.348
is when you experience the perfect love of God, when you rely upon, when you live in it, and then you share that perfect love with your neighbor, with the people that God has brought into your life, with people that you go out and find.

32:41.548 --> 32:49.841
When you share that perfect love with others, the fear go away, and you can live courageously for Jesus Christ.

32:51.323 --> 32:53.727
That is what God has called us to.

32:53.787 --> 32:55.570
Do you?

32:56.418 --> 32:57.139
One more time.

32:58.120 --> 33:01.264
Do you want to live a courageous life?

33:02.545 --> 33:05.429
Do you want to live a life full of courage?

33:07.391 --> 33:07.471
Yes.

33:07.491 --> 33:08.292
Do you want to be afraid?

33:10.956 --> 33:11.016
No.

33:11.036 --> 33:17.203
The encouragement this morning is live in the perfect love of God.

33:18.565 --> 33:20.507
Relie upon it.

33:20.527 --> 33:26.194
Know that He loves you from the top of your head to the tip of your toes inside and out.

33:27.874 --> 33:28.715
and then share it.

33:29.856 --> 33:43.131
Share that perfect love with all of those around you and watch your fears dissipate and your courage grow.

33:48.418 --> 33:55.826
I think most of us resonate with the cowardly lion because we all want more courage.

33:58.050 --> 34:06.841
The good news this morning is you don't have to walk a yellow brick road to the Emerald City to meet with the wizard.

34:08.463 --> 34:11.246
God Himself loves you.

34:12.407 --> 34:15.331
So there is nothing to be afraid of.

34:16.392 --> 34:23.861
And together we can journey, we can live this life encouraging each other to love other people.

34:24.902 --> 34:27.826
So along the journey, our fears

34:27.906 --> 34:30.195
will become less and less.

34:32.323 --> 34:39.029
And people will glorify God in heaven.

34:39.049 --> 34:39.410
Amen.

